 {"id":"charmed_rust-5vw","title":"[WASM] Add wasm feature flag and conditional compilation","description":"## Parent Epic
charmed_rust-64r: [EPIC] WebAssembly Support

## Objective
Add a `wasm` feature flag to all relevant crates and implement conditional compilation to exclude terminal-specific code when building for WebAssembly targets.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Add Feature Flags to Cargo.toml Files

```toml
# crates/lipgloss/Cargo.toml
[features]
default = []
wasm = ["wasm-bindgen", "web-sys"]

[dependencies]
wasm-bindgen = { version = "0.2", optional = true }
web-sys = { version = "0.3", optional = true, features = ["console"] }

[target.'cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))'.dependencies]
# Terminal-specific dependencies
termion = "2.0"
```

```toml
# crates/bubbletea/Cargo.toml
[features]
default = []
wasm = ["lipgloss/wasm", "wasm-bindgen"]

[target.'cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))'.dependencies]
crossterm = "0.27"
```

### 2. Conditional Compilation Patterns

```rust
// crates/lipgloss/src/lib.rs

#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
mod terminal;

#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
mod web;

// Re-export based on target
#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
pub use terminal::*;

#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
pub use web::*;
```

### 3. Guard Terminal-Specific Code

```rust
// crates/lipgloss/src/color.rs

impl Color {
    /// Convert to ANSI escape sequence (terminal only)
    #[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
    pub fn to_ansi_sequence(&self) -> String {
        match self {
            Color::Rgb(r, g, b) => format!("\x1b[38;2;{};{};{}m", r, g, b),
            Color::Ansi(code) => format!("\x1b[38;5;{}m", code),
            // ...
        }
    }

    /// Convert to CSS color string (WASM only)
    #[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
    pub fn to_css(&self) -> String {
        match self {
            Color::Rgb(r, g, b) => format!("rgb({}, {}, {})", r, g, b),
            Color::Ansi(code) => ansi_to_css(*code),
            // ...
        }
    }

    /// Convert to hex string (available on all platforms)
    pub fn to_hex(&self) -> String {
        match self {
            Color::Rgb(r, g, b) => format!("#{:02x}{:02x}{:02x}", r, g, b),
            // ...
        }
    }
}
```

### 4. Handle Platform-Specific Behavior

```rust
// crates/bubbletea/src/program.rs

#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
use crossterm::terminal;

#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
use crate::web::terminal_emulation;

impl Program {
    pub fn new(model: impl Model) -> Self {
        #[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
        {
            // Standard terminal setup
            terminal::enable_raw_mode().ok();
        }

        #[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
        {
            // Web-based setup (no raw mode needed)
            terminal_emulation::init();
        }

        Self { model, /* ... */ }
    }
}
```

### 5. Create Stub Implementations for Missing Features

```rust
// crates/bubbletea/src/web/mod.rs

#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
pub mod terminal_emulation {
    /// Initialize web terminal emulation
    pub fn init() {
        // Set up DOM elements or virtual terminal
    }

    /// Get terminal size (returns reasonable defaults for web)
    pub fn size() -> (u16, u16) {
        // Could query viewport or use fixed size
        (80, 24)
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All crates compile successfully with `--target wasm32-unknown-unknown`
- [ ] `cargo build` (native) still works without the wasm feature
- [ ] No terminal-specific code (ANSI escapes, raw mode) in WASM builds
- [ ] Feature flags are properly propagated through workspace dependencies
- [ ] CI includes WASM compilation check: `cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --features wasm`
- [ ] Documentation explains feature flag usage

## Implementation Notes
- Use `#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]` for target-based compilation
- Use `#[cfg(feature = "wasm")]` for feature-based optional dependencies
- Prefer target_arch checks for behavior changes, feature flags for dependencies
- Test both configurations in CI to prevent regressions
- Some crates (like `harmonica` for animations) may work unchanged

## Logging Requirements
```rust
use charmed_log::info;

#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
fn platform_init() {
    info!(target: "charmed::platform", "Initializing for WebAssembly target");
}

#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
fn platform_init() {
    info!(target: "charmed::platform", "Initializing for native terminal");
}
```

