## Objective
Implement table border rendering using lipgloss border styles, supporting various border characters and themes consistent with the glamour styling system.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Border Character Sets
Define border character sets for different styles:

```rust
/// Border characters for table rendering
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct TableBorder {
    pub top_left: &'static str,
    pub top_right: &'static str,
    pub bottom_left: &'static str,
    pub bottom_right: &'static str,
    pub horizontal: &'static str,
    pub vertical: &'static str,
    pub cross: &'static str,
    pub top_t: &'static str,
    pub bottom_t: &'static str,
    pub left_t: &'static str,
    pub right_t: &'static str,
}

/// Standard ASCII border
pub const ASCII_BORDER: TableBorder = TableBorder {
    top_left: "+",
    top_right: "+",
    bottom_left: "+",
    bottom_right: "+",
    horizontal: "-",
    vertical: "|",
    cross: "+",
    top_t: "+",
    bottom_t: "+",
    left_t: "+",
    right_t: "+",
};

/// Unicode rounded border (matches lipgloss RoundedBorder)
pub const ROUNDED_BORDER: TableBorder = TableBorder {
    top_left: "╭",
    top_right: "╮",
    bottom_left: "╰",
    bottom_right: "╯",
    horizontal: "─",
    vertical: "│",
    cross: "┼",
    top_t: "┬",
    bottom_t: "┴",
    left_t: "├",
    right_t: "┤",
};

/// Unicode normal border (matches lipgloss NormalBorder)
pub const NORMAL_BORDER: TableBorder = TableBorder {
    top_left: "┌",
    top_right: "┐",
    bottom_left: "└",
    bottom_right: "┘",
    horizontal: "─",
    vertical: "│",
    cross: "┼",
    top_t: "┬",
    bottom_t: "┴",
    left_t: "├",
    right_t: "┤",
};
```

### 2. Border Row Generation
Generate horizontal border rows:

```rust
fn render_horizontal_border(
    widths: &[usize],
    border: &TableBorder,
    position: BorderPosition,
) -> String {
    let (left, mid, right) = match position {
        BorderPosition::Top => (border.top_left, border.top_t, border.top_right),
        BorderPosition::Middle => (border.left_t, border.cross, border.right_t),
        BorderPosition::Bottom => (border.bottom_left, border.bottom_t, border.bottom_right),
    };

    let mut result = String::from(left);

    for (i, width) in widths.iter().enumerate() {
        // +2 for cell padding (space on each side)
        result.push_str(&border.horizontal.repeat(width + 2));
        if i < widths.len() - 1 {
            result.push_str(mid);
        }
    }

    result.push_str(right);
    result
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]
enum BorderPosition {
    Top,
    Middle,
    Bottom,
}
```

### 3. Integration with lipgloss Styles
Apply lipgloss styling to borders:

```rust
use lipgloss::Style;

/// Style configuration for table borders
pub struct TableStyle {
    pub border: TableBorder,
    pub border_style: Style,
    pub header_separator: bool,
    pub row_separator: bool,
}

impl Default for TableStyle {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            border: ROUNDED_BORDER,
            border_style: Style::new().foreground(lipgloss::Color::Ansi(240)),
            header_separator: true,
            row_separator: false,
        }
    }
}

fn render_border_line(line: &str, style: &Style) -> String {
    style.render(line)
}
```

### 4. Complete Table Rendering
Combine borders with cell content:

```rust
fn render_table(table: &ParsedTable, style: &TableStyle) -> String {
    let widths = calculate_column_widths(table);
    let mut lines = Vec::new();

    // Top border
    lines.push(render_horizontal_border(&widths, &style.border, BorderPosition::Top));

    // Header row
    lines.push(render_data_row(&table.header, &widths, &style.border));

    // Header separator
    if style.header_separator {
        lines.push(render_horizontal_border(&widths, &style.border, BorderPosition::Middle));
    }

    // Body rows
    for (i, row) in table.rows.iter().enumerate() {
        lines.push(render_data_row(row, &widths, &style.border));

        // Optional row separators (except after last row)
        if style.row_separator && i < table.rows.len() - 1 {
            lines.push(render_horizontal_border(&widths, &style.border, BorderPosition::Middle));
        }
    }

    // Bottom border
    lines.push(render_horizontal_border(&widths, &style.border, BorderPosition::Bottom));

    // Apply border style to all lines
    lines.iter()
        .map(|line| render_border_line(line, &style.border_style))
        .collect::<Vec<_>>()
        .join("\n")
}

fn render_data_row(cells: &[TableCell], widths: &[usize], border: &TableBorder) -> String {
    let mut result = String::from(border.vertical);

    for (i, cell) in cells.iter().enumerate() {
        let padded = pad_content(&cell.content, widths[i], cell.alignment);
        result.push_str(&format!(" {} ", padded));
        result.push_str(border.vertical);
    }

    result
}
```

### 5. Borderless Tables
Support tables without borders:

```rust
pub const NO_BORDER: TableBorder = TableBorder {
    top_left: "",
    top_right: "",
    bottom_left: "",
    bottom_right: "",
    horizontal: "",
    vertical: "",
    cross: "",
    top_t: "",
    bottom_t: "",
    left_t: "",
    right_t: "",
};

fn render_borderless_table(table: &ParsedTable) -> String {
    let widths = calculate_column_widths(table);
    let mut lines = Vec::new();

    // Header
    lines.push(render_borderless_row(&table.header, &widths));

    // Separator line (dashes)
    let separator: String = widths.iter()
        .map(|w| "-".repeat(*w))
        .collect::<Vec<_>>()
        .join(" ");
    lines.push(separator);

    // Body rows
    for row in &table.rows {
        lines.push(render_borderless_row(row, &widths));
    }

    lines.join("\n")
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

1. **ASCII Borders**: Render tables with +, -, | characters
2. **Unicode Borders**: Render tables with box-drawing characters
3. **Rounded Borders**: Support rounded corner characters
4. **Header Separator**: Distinct line between header and body
5. **Border Styling**: Apply lipgloss colors to border characters
6. **Borderless Mode**: Support tables without visible borders
7. **Alignment Preservation**: Borders don't affect cell alignment

## Implementation Notes

- Border characters are always single-width for alignment
- Use consistent spacing: one space padding inside each cell
- Consider terminal unicode support for fallback to ASCII
- Border style should be configurable per-table or globally
- Integrate with glamour's theme system for consistent styling

